<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 30 at 2:15AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...REDUCED VISIBILITY AND LOCALIZED ACCUMULATION IN BURSTS OF
HEAVIER SNOW EARLY THIS MORNING...
Several narrow bands of briefly heavier snowfall will continue to
track across the area early this morning. The potential exists
for the heaviest bursts of snow to result in a rapid reduction in
visibility below 1 mile and a quick accumulation of snow on
roadways. Use caution while driving tonight and allow extra time
to reach your destination. Be prepared for variable road
conditions and lowered visibilities.</description>
